task.name: eni is you
task.solution:
The title is an obvious reference to the indy hit game "baba is you" and works in  the same way.  Each level is completed by stepping on a block that has the win proberty. 
In the first level this is the check mark on the right. Pushing the eureka (light bulb) away clears a path to the answer.
In the second level the rule "wall is stop" needs to be seperated to be able to walk across the wall. 
In the third level the rule "wall is stop" also has to be seperated, and in adition the "is" block from "wall is stop" needs to be pushed between "answer" and "win" to create a block with the "win" property.

task.name: Beat it!
task.solution:
The episode numbers of the video contain the A1Z26 encoded message "intro has clue". Watching the intro will leed you to a section where the player signals the word "chat" using semaphore. The semaphore code is hinted by the tasks message "has  been flagged".

The single chat message of the video is
Farnsworth019 - "Good news everybody! - he missed the block."
Which is a reference to a character from Futurama and links to the beat saber video for the futurama intro theme. The number in the username encodes a timestamp in the video using the format: xyy -> x:yy. The futurama video at the timecode 0:19  shows another semaphore symbol and the video contains another chat message. Following this chain of username - song reference in this way yields the following letters.

Carameldansen:  Farnsworth019 
Q  Futurama 0:19 - PirateHunter114
U One Piece 1:14 - olaf319
A Frozen 3:19 - Rival055
D Pokemon 0:55 - secondchild228
R Neon Genesis Evangelion 2:28 - MagicalGirl057
A Sailor Moon  0:57 - Jou013
C Digimon 0:13 - RichUncle143
E Ducktales 1:43 - plumber040
# Super Mario Bors. 0:40 - oag139
2 Call me maybe 1:39 - Geralt151
0 Witcher 1:51 - Enigma140
1 Dota 1:40 - TimeTraveller135
6 Your Name

Searching for a quad race in 2016 at the location set for the videos (buenos aires) will lead you the the dacar rally of 2016. The winner of its quad category is the answer.

Fort Counterclockwise

There are 6 letters to decipher going counterclockwise each encoded by a set of 4 small towers. 
We start with the uppermost set denoted by the longest line of shells. 
Each set of towers is read counterclockwise. The starting point is to outermost tower when viewed from the center of the castle as indicated by the line of shells going outward. This yields: 

1212
1230
1233
1313
1211
1302

The title hints (Fort) to read these numbers in base 4 which are then all in the range of ASCII characters

102 f
108 l
111 o
119 w
101 e
114 r

giving the solution

task.name: OnIoN
task.content:
BYECIANNGSOTNIYLO
MpxbdcppocooxppxL
Ac*36*12*97*61*bU
Od*HordeRotsOn8cG
Do6sTHECENTERB6bR
Mc6aeSkcihTuae*dE
Lb4181*722*4862cK
MbxppcdcxbocpobbT
LOARDFRWAOOWBAYUE
task.solution:
The name OnIoN suggests to do something with evers second letter as well as that onions come in layers from the outside to the inside. The first layer read clockwise "BYECIANNGSOTNIYLOLUGREKTEUYABWOOAWRFDRAOLMLMDOAM" spells "being on your keyboard all day can still get u a wow from mom".

This is the key to the next layer: "keyboard" hints at looking at your keyboard, WOW from MOM can be generated by flipping all letters upside down.
Applying this logic to the next layer, it reads:
pxbdcppo cooxppxb cbdcbbop cobxcdcp pxbbcodc (Already formated ASCII like). Flipping the letters upside down, it reads
bxpqcbbo cooxbbxp cpqcppob copxcqcb bxppcoqc. If you look at a keyboard, it only uses the top and bottom row only. Using top = 1 and bottom = 0 gives 00110001 01100001 01101110 01100100 00110110 which equals "1and6".

Checking which numbers are 1 or 6 in the next line give you a decomposition into true or false which can further be transformed to morse: If the number is a 1 or 6 we use a dash and if it is not, we use a dot. The  * symbol separates the morse sequences.
*36*12*97*61* 86* 2684*227*181466*
  .-     -.      ..   - -     .-      .-..      ...      - . -. - - 
Spelling "animals!"

Looking at the last layer, it spells Horde Rots On Beau Thick Seas. For each, 1 letter can be changed to spell an animal: Horse Rats Ox Bear Chick Seal.
The letters which were changed give: donuts.

The Center of donuts is a hole or holes, which is the solution.

task.name: Elizabeth
task.content:
<video height="800" width="800" controls loop>
  <source src="https://enig.ma.tum.de/static/2020W/elizabeth/Elizabeth.mp4" type="video/mp4;">
Your browser does not support the video tag.
</video>
task.solution:
Elizabeth

The animation consists of three rings with notches and teeth. Reading each notch as . and tooth as - we obtain
- .... . .-. . .. ... .- .-.. .-- .- -.-- ... .- .-.. .. --. .... - .... --- ..- ... .
for the othermost ring starting at 12 o'clock reading clockwise which is morse for THERE IS ALWAYS A LIGHTHOUSE
- .... . .-. . .. ... .- .-.. .-- .- -.-- ... .- -- .- -.
for the middle ring starting at 12 o'clock reading counterclockwise which is morse for THERE IS ALWAYS A MAN and
- .... . .-. . .. ... .- .-.. .-- .- -.-- ... .- -.-. .. - -.--
for the inner ring starting at 6 o'clock reading clockwise which is morse for THERE IS ALWAYS A CITY.
All sentences combined form a quote of the character Elizabeth of the game Bioshock Infinite.

Interpreting the five blinking circles as lighthouses, we obtain the light characteristics (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Light_characteristic) following the outer morse circle (starting at 12 o'clock top continuing clockwise)

Fl(2) W 10s 
Oc W 10s
L.Fl W 10s
Iso W 10s
Al WO 10s

Reading the first letters, we obtain FOLIA (eureka).

Reading the numbers of the middle ring in order of the notches and teeth, we obtain
04021615
As we are looking for a man, this can be interpreted as a date, i.e., 04-02-1615 which is day of death of Giambattista della Porta (eureka), the inventor of the porta cipher.

Combining the encryption method (porta cipher) with the key (folia) and using it on the lock (text in the center), we decrypt the text starting to read at 6 o'clock continuing clockwise
TTUXHGOZZHCWZIJYAZINCWUCNGVPRGPVLLEYRKKLWXQJLDBJZRHOJN
to
I AM BURIED UNDERWATER AND MY ARCHITECTURAL STYLE IS YOUR DESIRE

As we are looking for a city, we realize that there is an underwater city called Rapture in the Bioshock game series which is built in the ART DECO (solution) style.

task.solution:
64 letters sorted in a square give a chess board pattern/grid. Looking at the spaces per line in asci (space after letter or no space after letter -> 0 and 1)i, it spells openings. In the grid, you can read the words "vienna", "bird" and "catalan". Each are chess openings. Looking at how white moves its pieces in these openings (start and end positions of each move), each opening spells a word:
Vienne opening: Kiss
Bird's opening: Me
Catalan Opening: Deadly

task.name: eni is you
task.solution:
The level can be solved by moving the eurekas so that they block the plague from reaching the right side of the map. Afterwards "plague" can be moved down to create the rule "plague is push" and clear a path to the answer. Solving the level gives you instruction to send a message to the bot on discord.

To get the right message that will trigger a reaction from the bot, take the title of the stage "plumage engirt" and apply the rules encircled by the birds to it. The rules are "eni is you" and "plague is spread", which are to be read as p -> s, l -> p , a -> r and so on. Replacing the letters this way transforms "plumage engirt" to "spamred yogurt".  Sending red yogurt 3 times to the bot will give you the answer.

task.name: doctor count
task.content:
<video height="640" width="540" controls loop>
  <source src="https://enig.ma.tum.de/static/2020W/pd/namesquare.mp4" type="video/mp4;">
Your browser does not support the video tag.
</video>
task.solution:
The video starts with "Strange Doctor" and shots of crows and a moon. Crow moon denotes the full moon in march. 
On the stone in the next shot one can see a cross and 1815. I n 1815 the march full moon was 25th - 20 days earlier is march 5th 1815. The day Franz "Mesmer" died.

The next card says "A Count" . The plague doctor's staf blinks morse code for "Tyr, Hagal, Freya", the names of the rune aetts. in cipher runes each rune is denoted by the number of its aett and its position in the aett. The Position of the plague doctor's hand on the staf denotes the aett, the fingers show the number in the aett. This spells  "Kaunt Rukin" - minding the fact that the younger furthark  has not all letters our alphabet provides  - "count Rugen", the 6-fingered villain from the Pricess Bride. 

The next card says "Count A". counting the "a"'s in the three sentences of on the parchment gives: 1-12-5 or "Ale", as in Ale the Strong, who is also described by the text. 

The card after that says "Doctor Strange". The reversed hour glass, gives that THE "Doctor Strange" is meant.

That the audio contains tap code (there is no "audio is for atmosphere only" in the metadata).
The woodblock sound in the audio is knock code for 
the man - the actor - the man - the actor - fivebyfive. In the respective parts of the video, leaving us with
mesmer (the man)
guest (the actor playing Rugen)
ale (the man)
cumberbatch  (the actor playing Doctor Strange)

The last part of the video is "A Square".
putting the 25 letters  (five by five)  of the name (the video is named "namesquare") in a square and marking the letters in the pattern crossed on the parchment, gives the solution "mega leech".
